questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application running on a Tomcat container experiences a gradual `java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Metaspace` after dynamic plugins are loaded and unloaded repeatedly. You isolate the classloading code to this snippet:

java
public class PluginLoader {
    private static final ThreadLocal<PluginContext> contextHolder = new ThreadLocal<>();

    public void executePlugin(String jarPath) throws Exception {
        URLClassLoader tempLoader = new URLClassLoader(new URL[]{new File(jarPath).toURI().toURL()});
        Class<?> clazz = tempLoader.loadClass("com.example.DynamicPlugin");
        PluginContext context = (PluginContext) clazz.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();
        contextHolder.set(context);
        context.run();
        // Attempting clean up
        tempLoader.close();
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a low-latency microservice experiences severe latency spikes during intensive batch operations. The JVM GC logs show very short young-generation pause times (under 5ms), but the application-level metrics report pauses exceeding 200ms. You suspect a Time-To-Safepoint (TTSP) delay. You locate the following hot path method:

java
public void processTelemetryData(List<TelemetryRecord> records) {
    for (long i = 0; i < records.size(); i++) {
        // Highly intensive mathematical and cryptographic operations
        processRecordValue(records.get((int) i));
    }
}
